lead_paragraph: Anja Hüber of Germany edged Katie Uhlaender of the United States to win the world skeleton title in Altenberg, Germany. Hüber, the European champion, finished her four runs in a combined 4:02.78. Uhlaender, the World Cup overall champion, was 0.30 back.
